_rawBody:
Marianne sells photos.

\begin{parts}
\item The selling price of each photo is \$6.

\begin{subparts}
\item The selling price for each photo is made up of two parts, printing cost and profit.\\
For each photo, the ratio printing cost : profit = 5 : 3.

Calculate the profit she makes on each photo.

\AnswerLine[][\$]
\Marks{2}

\item Calculate her profit as a percentage of the selling price.

\AnswerLine[][\%]
\Marks{1}

\item Calculate the selling price of a photo in euros (€) when the exchange rate is €1 = \$1.091 .

\AnswerLine[][€]
\Marks{2}
\end{subparts}

\item Marianne sells two sizes of photo.\\
These photos are mathematically similar rectangles.\\
The smaller photo has length 15 cm and width 12 cm.\\
The larger photo has area 352.8 cm$^2$.

Calculate the length of the larger photo.

\AnswerLine[][cm]
\Marks{3}

\item In a sale, Marianne buys a new camera for \$483.\\
This is a reduction of 8\% on the original price.

Calculate the original price of the camera.

\AnswerLine[][\$]
\Marks{3}
\end{parts}

